Tip Added on : 29-05-2020
Css Scoping in React
Step1: execute *react-scripts eject*
Step2: Navigate to Config Folder(it will only created once above command completed execution)
Step3: open webpack.config.dev.js
    1) we have one block for css handling under that we have objects named ad options
	2) under options object add following properties
	     modules: true,
         localIdentName: '[name]__[local]__[hash:base64:5]'
Step4: repeat Step 3 for webpack.config.prod.js as well
Step5: Stop Application and run again after executing command *npm install*
-----------------------------